
This repo demonstrates how to build a linux/arm64 docker image of OpenMalaria.

- Follow instructions here https://docs.docker.com/guides/gha/ for using GitHub Actions to do Docker image builds.
- Use OpenMalaria Dockerfile instead of sample Dockerfile provided at above page.
- Modify docker-ci.yml to use ubuntu-24.04-arm instead of ubuntu-latest.
- Modify git clone command in Dockerfile to use a branch/tag which supports linux/arm64 (shema-48.0 does not support linux/arm64).

